title: Grateful Dead Live at Oakland-Alameda County Coliseum on 1991-02-19
lineage: Cassette Master (Nakamichi CR-7A) > Tascam DA-3000 (DSF 1-bit/5.6 MHz) >KORG AudioGate 4 > Samplitude Pro X3 Suite > FLAC/24
description:
Set 1

Bertha, Greatest Story Ever Told, Althea, Queen Jane Approximately, Ramble On Rose, Picasso Moon, Peggy-O, Cassidy, New Speedway Boogie

Set 2

China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Truckin'-> Crazy Fingers-> Jam-> Drums-> Jam-> The Wheel-> All Along The Watchtower-> Black Peter-> Sugar Magnolia, E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text: POOR MIX Despite Charlie Miller's great job, as always, the actual mix coming off the board has Bobby's guitar way too loud at times.  Check the concluding jam on ALTHEA where Jerry is on fire, but Bobby's guitar is louder than his.  There is only one audience source available and that one sounds like it was recorded in the bathroom.  A real good audience copy will hopefully surface and perhaps lead to a great Matrix.  The show is a 5 star all the way, but the mix is 2 stars at best.
